comments.body:
The connection to voyager fails because this block of code takes too long. https://github.com/pulibrary/voyager_helpers/blob/e3c830c68d7f2a8fdde8dcfc8339c5f1381532b3/lib/voyager_helpers/liberator.rb#L526
```
unless item_statuses.include?('In Process')
  item_barcode = get_barcode_from_item(item, c)
   barcodes << item_barcode
end
```
Tested it locally. Set a timestamp with a 24hrs difference. 
`TIMESTAMP="2020-10-05 19:00" bundle exec rake marc_liberation:recap_dump` I had commented out the part of the code that uploads the file to scsb.
number of items it counted: 37,351 (`items = updated_recap_items(date, c)`)
  started retrieving items: 2020-10-06T20:09:21-04:00
  Finished retrieving items: 2020-10-06T20:10:07-04:00
Entered the loop: 2020-10-06T20:10:07-04:00 Looping through items
Failed with `ORA-12170: TNS:Connect timeout occurred` at : 2020-10-06T21:39:27.709679. 
When it failed it had counted: barcodes.count: 5429

Log file: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1CKIaBRyUgUXW4iNWd5Yf0S0SsdKhdJBX/view?usp=sharing
I have refactored VoyagerHelpers::Liberator.updated_recap_barcodes in a voyager_helpers branch (scsb_export). What remains is refactoring the code that dumps the records to files.
